Kajol and Twinkle are serving up a talk show with a twist - equal parts masti, magic and maybe even some manic energy. Expect wild hot takes, controversial opinions and the kind of honesty that makes you say, “Dude, same!”

title: Is there real money in Kannada content creation? | Episode 4 | Ft.Vickypedia and Raghu Vine Store
description:
Can you really build a career just by creating content? 🤔 How much does a YouTube creator in India actually earn if a video hits 100K views? What does it take to leave a safe IT job and go all in as a full time creator entrepreneur? And is there a playbook for building a team, scaling reach, and making viral content consistently on Instagram and YouTube?

In this episode of Mundhe Banni, we explore the Creator Economy through the lens of entrepreneurship with two of Kannada’s biggest creators, @vickypediakannada5412  and @RaghuVinestore 
Both started solo, both took the leap from IT jobs, and today they are not just entertainers but entrepreneurs who run small teams, and show us what it takes to thrive in the Creator Economy.

This episode is filled with laughter, learnings, and the real playbook for turning creativity into a business.

If you are curious about the future of entrepreneurship in regional content, this one is a must watch.

Inspiration is like happiness, it grows when you share it. Share this episode.!!

ಕನ್ನಡದಲ್ಲಿ:
ಕನ್ನಡದಲ್ಲಿ ವಿಡಿಯೋ ಕಂಟೆಂಟ್ ಮಾಡಿ ಬದುಕು ಕಟ್ಟಿಕೊಳ್ಳಬಹುದಾ? ಒಂದು ವಿಡಿಯೋಗೆ ಯುಟ್ಯೂಬ್ ಅಲ್ಲಿ ಒಂದು ಲಕ್ಷ ವಿವ್ಸ್ ಬಂದ್ರೆ ಭಾರತದಲ್ಲಿ ಒಬ್ಬ ಕ್ರಿಯೇಟರ್ ಎಷ್ಟು ದುಡ್ಡು ಮಾಡ್ತಾನೆ? ಐ.ಟಿ ಕೆಲಸ ಬಿಟ್ಟು ಕಂಟೆಂಟ್ ಅನ್ನೇ ವೃತ್ತಿಯಾಗಿಸಿಕೊಂಡು ಒಂದು ಸಣ್ಣ ಉದ್ದಿಮೆ ತರಹ ಕಟ್ಟಲು ಸಾಧ್ಯವೇ? ಮತ್ತೆ ಮತ್ತೆ ವೈರಲ್ ಆಗುವ ವಿಡಿಯೋಗಳನ್ನು ಸೃಷ್ಟಿ ಮಾಡಲು ಏನಾದರೂ ಫಾರ್ಮುಲಾ ಇದೆಯಾ? 

ಕನ್ನಡದ ಅತ್ಯಂತ ಜನಪ್ರಿಯ ಮತ್ತು ಯಶಸ್ವಿ ಕಂಟೆಂಟ್ ಕ್ರಿಯೇಟರ್ಸ್ ವಿಕಿಪೀಡಿಯಾ ಖ್ಯಾತಿಯ ವಿಕಾಸ್ ಮತ್ತು ರಘು ವೈನ್ ಸ್ಟೋರ್ ಖ್ಯಾತಿಯ ರಘು ಗೌಡವರೊಡನೆ ಕನ್ನಡದ ಕ್ರಿಯೇಟರ್ ಎಕನಾಮಿಯ ಸಾಧ್ಯತೆ, ಸವಾಲು, ಅವಕಾಶಗಳ ಕುರಿತು ಒಂದು ಮಾಸ್ಟರ್ ಕ್ಲಾಸ್ ಪಾಡ್ಕಾಸ್ಟ್ ಇಲ್ಲಿದೆ. 

ಇಲ್ಲಿ ನಗೆಯಿದೆ, ಜನ ಮೆಚ್ಚಿದ ಕ್ರಿಯೇಟರ್ ಆಗುವ ಪಯಣದ ಏಳು ಬೀಳುಗಳಿವೆ, ಎಲ್ಲಕ್ಕೂ ಮಿಗಿಲಾಗಿ ಕನ್ನಡದ ಕ್ರಿಯೇಟರ್ ಎಕನಾಮಿ ಹೇಗಿದೆ, ಏನೆಲ್ಲ ಅವಕಾಶಗಳಿವೆ, ಸವಾಲುಗಳಿವೆ ಮತ್ತು ಇದರ ಮುಂದಿನ ದಿನಗಳು ಹೇಗಿವೆ ಅನ್ನುವ ಕುರಿತು ಆಳವಾದ ಒಳನೋಟಗಳಿವೆ.

ಖುಶಿ ಒಬ್ಬರೇ ಪಡಬಾರದು. ಈ ಸಂಚಿಕೆ ನಿಮ್ಮ ಗೆಳೆಯರಿಗೂ ಹಂಚುವುದನ್ನು ಮರೆಯಬೇಡಿ

description:
Prime Video India Presents
Two Much With Kajol And Twinkle Official Teaser
Starring Kajol and Twinkle Khanna
Created by Banijay Asia

Official Release Date September 25, 2025 on Prime Video India.

About:
Kajol and Twinkle are serving up a talk show with a twist - equal parts masti, magic and maybe even some manic energy. Expect wild hot takes, controversial opinions and the kind of honesty that makes you say, “Dude, same!” 
Joining them are their friends who just happen to be some of the biggest stars in the country (and even the world). With eight unique pairs gracing the couch this season, the conversations jump from filmy nostalgia to family drama, love, paparazzi, fame and everything in between.
What sets it apart is the unapologetic female gaze - a perspective that’s funny, sharp, and not afraid to hold up a mirror to society. One moment you’re laughing embarrassingly loudly, the next you’re caught off guard by an insight that might make you question your own life choices. 
Basically, it’s a vibe: two women side-by-side, yapping with their friends. Think of it as the fun table at the party, sunny, chatty, and just unhinged enough to keep you hooked.

title: Can Your Portfolio Adapt to the Markets? | Groww Multi Asset Allocation Fund NFO
description:
Markets don’t stay the same.
At times equities rally, in other phases debt performs better, and during uncertainty, gold or silver take the lead. The challenge? No single asset class works across all market cycles.

That’s where a multi-asset approach can help. By combining equity, debt, gold, and silver within one portfolio — and adjusting allocations as markets change — investors can aim for better diversification and potentially better risk-adjusted returns over the long term.

The Groww Multi Asset Allocation Fund is built on this very idea. It also uses Groww Mutual Fund’s proprietary platform, SHAASTRA (Strategic Holistic Asset Allocation and Systematic Technical Risk Assessment), which supports fund managers with data-driven insights to make allocation decisions more structured and less prone to human biases.

title: Introducing iPhone 17 Pro | Apple
description:
Introducing iPhone 17 Pro. Built from solid aluminum, a unique unibody encases our biggest battery with our longest battery life. The most powerful chip made for iPhone is cooled by an entirely new thermal system. Ceramic Shield protects the back as well as the front, and the display is 3x more scratch resistant. title: Introducing AirPods Pro 3 | Apple
description:
The world’s best in-ear Active Noise Cancellation, with up to 2x more noise cancelled than AirPods Pro 2. Exceptional sound quality. All-new heart rate sensing during workouts. A more secure in-ear fit. IP57 dust, sweat, and water resistance. A clinical-grade Hearing Aid feature. Live Translation to communicate across languages. And improved battery life with up to 8 hours of listening time.

Learn More: https://apple.co/3If6cDp

“BLUH BLUH BLUH” by _BY.ALEXANDER https://apple.co/BLUH-BLUH-BLUH

#AirPods #AirPodsPro3 #AppleEvent 

World’s best Active Noise Cancellation evaluation tested in July 2025 in accordance with IEC 60268-24 as compared with best-selling commercially available wireless in-ear headphones.

Built-in heart rate monitor is intended for use during workouts with the Fitness app and compatible third-party apps on iPhone running iOS 26 and later.

AirPods Pro 3 are dust, sweat, and water resistant for non-water sports and exercise.

The Hearing Aid feature has received FDA authorization. This feature is supported on AirPods Pro 2 and later with the latest firmware when paired with a compatible iPhone, iPad, or Mac with iOS 18, iPadOS 18, or macOS Sequoia and later, and is intended for people 18 years old or older with perceived mild to moderate hearing loss.

Live Translation works when paired with an Apple Intelligence–enabled iPhone running iOS 26 and later. Supports English (UK, U.S.), French (France), German, Portuguese (Brazil), and Spanish (Spain). For more information, see https://www.apple.com/ios/feature-availability/. 

Battery life depends on device settings, environment, usage, and many other factors.

title: Pehla Pyaar, Pehla Heartbreak 💔 | Akshay Kumar, Aishwarya Rai Bachchan, Alia Bhatt, Ranbir Kapoor
description:
First love feels like discovering fire for the very first time. Everything burns brighter, every touch leaves an echo, every word feels sacred. You go to school just to see them smile in the hallway, and suddenly that smile is the most important sight in the world. You stay awake until sunrise because their voice feels better than sleep itself. Every song makes sense, every poem speaks your truth, every star in the sky seems less beautiful than they are. You’d choose them in this universe and in every universe that could ever exist. In their presence, time bends, pain disappears, and forever feels like something you can finally hold in your hands. You think this is it, the kind of love poets spent lifetimes chasing, the kind of love that could never be broken.
But then life happens. Distance grows where closeness once lived. Silence floods the places where laughter once echoed. The person who was once your entire world becomes a stranger you still dream about at night. The same memories that once made you smile now burn like open wounds that refuse to heal. You replay conversations in your head, wonder what you could have said, what you could have done differently. Maybe it wasn’t meant to be. Maybe the timing was cruel. Maybe the world was too heavy on two young hearts. And so, you’re left staring at your phone, almost typing their name, before remembering that they are no longer yours to reach.
The hardest part isn’t losing them. It’s learning how to exist without them. Waking up every day and remembering all over again that they are gone. Carrying a love that has nowhere to rest, like water slipping endlessly through your hands. Yet somehow, you keep breathing, you keep walking, you keep living with a heart that is shattered but still beating, broken but still full of hope. Because even after the fire fades, something inside you still aches to believe that beauty will return.
Sometimes, the love we cannot live without is the very love we must learn to survive without. ❤‍?

Upcoming Phones of September 2025 📱🔥
September 2025 is set to be the biggest smartphone launch month of the year, with major brands bringing their flagship and mid-range killers to India and global markets. From Apple’s iPhone 17 Series to the latest Vivo, Samsung, iQOO, Oppo, and Realme phones, this lineup is packed with innovation, performance, and cutting-edge design.

✨Confirmed & Expected Launches in September 2025

Apple iPhone 17, iPhone 17 Pro, iPhone 17 Air – A18 Bionic, iOS 19, new Liquid Glass design, AI-powered Apple Intelligence.

Samsung Galaxy S25 FE – Affordable flagship with Galaxy AI, Snapdragon 8 Gen 4, and top-tier display.

Vivo X300 & Vivo V60e – Next-gen Vivo X series with ZEISS cameras and powerful performance.

iQOO 15 – Performance beast with Snapdragon 8 Gen 4, built for gamers and power users.

Realme 15T – Budget-friendly 5G phone with strong performance for under ₹25,000.

Redmi Note 15 Pro – Flagship features at mid-range pricing, AMOLED + 200MP camera expected.

Oppo F31 & Oppo Find X9 Ultra – Stylish mid-range phone + premium flagship with advanced AI cameras.

🔍 Why September 2025 is Huge for Smartphones?
This month covers every segment — from flagship iPhones for premium buyers to budget-friendly Realme, Redmi, and Oppo phones for value seekers. title: No Frame Missed | Apple
description:
The simple act of filming can be challenging for people with Parkinson’s. Often they are unable to capture their own memories.

For Brett, Bette, and Ellen, every moment matters. With Action mode on iPhone, they can capture smooth hand-held videos and reclaim the joy of filming their favorite moments — supported by accessibility features like Voice Control, which help them operate the camera and navigate their iPhone with ease.

“For someone like me, who’s been using cameras for 30 years, it being an option again is kind of life-changing.” — Brett
